          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">Trump’s legal games</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-12-1.jpg" alt="Trump’s legal games" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Manhattan prosecutors have <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20241211-prosecutors-restate-opposition-to-trump-bid-to-dismiss-hush-money-conviction" target="_blank">opposed</a> President-elect Donald Trump’s latest attempt to dismiss his conviction for concealing hush money payments to an adult film star during his 2016 campaign. While rejecting his motion to vacate the guilty verdict, they agreed to pause the case during his presidency to avoid interference with his second term, set to begin on January 20. Judge Juan Merchan postponed sentencing after Trump’s November 5 election victory.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Trump’s legal team cited a Supreme Court <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/07/01/politics/presidents-immunity-supreme-court-what-matters/index.html" target="_blank">ruling</a> granting presidents broad immunity as justification. Still, prosecutors argued that a stay of proceedings is sufficient and that Trump's bid to have the case thrown out was "well beyond" what was needed to protect the presidency.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
